
<Lesson stage="2" page="4" type="Reading Check">
<APageParagraph activityIntroClip="uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3"  pencil="p3" skipIntro="true">
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Now, many years ago, Paul Bunyan was born in Maine.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He was so big his howls made fish jump and his clapping made windows shake.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He was so big he had to curl up in a lumber truck to sleep.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
		 <text>His parents took him to live in the woods where he grew up.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
	  <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>One winter it was so cold the snow was blue.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Paul was staring at this odd sight.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
	   <sentence>
	     <text>He found an animal stuck in a snow drift.</text>
	     <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		  <text>It was a baby ox, so he brought it back home with him.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		  <text>The next day, the ox was warm and dry but it had blue hair.</text>
	     <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		  <text>Paul kept his blue ox and called him Babe.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		  <text>Soon, Babe was the biggest ox there was.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
	   <sentence>
		 <text>Paul had Babe help with his work and they made a very good team.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	   </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Paul and Babe went on to live and work in the logging camps.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Paul set up his own camp near the banks of a river.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The camp was so big, you needed a basket of food with you to walk from one side to the other.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  </paragraph>
  <paragraph>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
         <text>People say Paul Bunyan made the shape of this land.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		 <text>Others say he and Babe cut down all the trees from North and South Dakota.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		<text>Some say, he went as far as Alaska.</text>
	    <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		 <text>It all rests on the teller and the tale.</text>
		 <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
